post_text:
The Texas Match the Promise Foundation℠ encourages families to save for college by offering competitive matching scholarships and tuition grants to students who are beneficiaries of a Texas Tuition Promise Fund® account — the state's prepaid college tuition plan.

Match the Promise scholarships help young Texans realize their dreams of a college education while also encouraging families to take steps now to prepare for their children's futures.

To apply for a scholarship, the Promise Fund beneficiary must be in grade five through nine and have a family income of $100,000 or less. Students must write a career essay and meet residency and other requirements.

The Foundation accepts scholarship applications Sept. 1 through Dec. 31. Families also can enroll in the Promise Fund during the scholarship application period if they have not already done so.

Match the Promise is funded by generous contributions from citizens, building a stronger Texas for tomorrow.

https://comptroller.texas.gov/programs/education/match/

post_text:
Galena Park ISD resumes meal service for students today. We will offer two options for meal distribution to accommodate as many students as possible.
The first option is a curbside service to help accommodate working parents' schedules. This option will be offered twice per week on Tuesdays and Thursdays from 4:00 p.m. – 6:00 p.m.
The second option is a bus delivery system with designated sites and stops. Bus delivery will be on Tuesdays and Thursdays from 9:30 a.m. to 11:30 a.m. The parent or guardian may be present, with or without their child(ren) to receive meals. If the parent is not present, the child(ren) will need to present one of the following items:
Student ID number
Student ID card
Official letter/ email from your child's campus
If you choose the bus option and miss your pick-up, you can stop by a curbside site to pick up your meals. You may only participate once per delivery day.

For more information, please visit our Meal Distribution Information webpage at https://www.galenaparkisd.com/Page/9236.

post_text:
Galena Park I.S.D. reanuda hoy el servicio de comidas para los estudiantes. Ofreceremos dos opciones para la distribución de comidas para acomodar a tantos estudiantes como sea posible.
La primera opción es un servicio en la acera para ayudar a acomodar los horarios de los padres que trabajan. Esta opción se ofrecerá dos veces por semana los martes y jueves de 4:00 p.m. a 6:00 p.m.
La segunda opción es un sistema de entrega en autobuses con sitios y paradas designadas. La entrega en autobús será los martes y jueves de 9:30 a.m. a 11:30 a.m. El padre o tutor puede estar presente, con o sin su/s hijo/s para recibir las comidas. Si el padre no está presente, el niño deberá presentar uno de los siguientes elementos:
Número de identificación del estudiante
Tarjeta de identificación de estudiante
Carta oficial / correo electrónico de la escuela de su hijo
Si elige la opción de autobús y pierde su recogida, puede pasar por un sitio junto a la acera para recoger sus comidas. Solo puede participar una vez por día de entrega.

post_text:
Good afternoon! Thankfully, our area was spared by Hurricane Laura. However, Galena Park I.S.D. remains closed through Friday, August 28, and will reopen on Monday, August 31. This message is to inform our school community that our five curbside meal locations will be open for meal distribution Friday, August 28, 2020, from 10:30 a.m. - 12:00 noon, or while supplies last. As a reminder, our five curbside meal distribution locations are Tice Elementary, Woodland Acres Elementary, Galena Park Elementary, North Shore Middle School, and Sam Houston Elementary School.

Friday's meal distribution will be the last one for the summer. Galena Park ISD's Student Nutrition Department will be transitioning to our virtual school meal program next week and preparing to begin serving our students on September 8th. Thank you to those who have used the curbside meal distribution service, and we look forward to providing delicious, nutritious meals to our students beginning again on September 8th.

As a reminder, our five curbside meal distribution locations are Tice Elementary, Woodland Acres Elementary, Galena Park Elementary, North Shore Middle School, and Sam Houston Elementary School.

Friday's meal distribution will be the last one for the summer. Galena Park ISD's Student Nutrition Department will be transitioning to our virtual school meal program next week and preparing to begin serving our students on September 8th. Thank you to those who have used the curbside meal distribution service, and we look forward to providing delicious, nutritious meals to our students beginning again on September 8th.

Dual credit workshops will be held on Wednesday, August 19th and Thursday, August 20th for students. The sessions will be held via Zoom. During the workshop, students will be provided assistance in setting up their Secure Online System (SOS) account, setting up their email accounts, and review how to access Blackboard and its features. The workshops are only for students who need assistance with these programs.

Students may attend one of the sessions listed below:
Session I: Wednesday, August 19th – 9 a.m.
Session II: Wednesday, August 19th – 6 p.m.
Session III: Thursday, August 20th – 9 a.m.
Session IV: Thursday, August 20th – 6 p.m.

post_text:
It’s time for Kroger’s annual school supply drive – Backpack Boosters!

Backpack Boosters helps provide school supply kits filled with the essential school supplies students need to start the school year off right – whether that’s in a classroom or through home learning. Galena Park I.S.D students will be recipients of the Backpack Boosters.

From July 15 through August 2, donate a prepackaged school supply kit for $7, or simply donate $2, $5 or $10 dollars at the register in any Kroger store to help local students. This is your chance to make a difference in the lives of students and to help them maximize their learning potential.

#KrogerCares #GalenaParkISDExcellence

From July 15 through August 2, donate a prepackaged school supply kit for $7, or simply donate $2, $5 or $10 dollars at the register in any Kroger store to help local students. This is your chance to make a difference in the lives of students and to help them maximize their learning potential.

#KrogerCares #GalenaParkISDExcellence

Galena Park I.S.D. will again utilize Skyward Family Access for parents/guardians to complete Returning Student Verification (RSV). All currently enrolled students who will be attending a GPISD school for the 2020 - 2021 school year are required to complete RSV Skyward Online Registration. The online registration process will allow parents to verify and update contact, emergency and health information for each child. This online registration process will be available on July 20th – July 24th.

For the 2020-2021 school year, proof of residence is only required if you have changed your address. Proof of residence (water, gas, electric bill or lease) can be attached electronically in Skyward.

Mustang Football Update:

Due to ongoing uncertainty regarding the Covid-19 pandemic, including potential travel restrictions and challenges, Paragon Marketing Group and ESPN has decided not to move forward with plans for De La Salle High School (CA) and St. Joseph's Prep (PA) to travel to Texas for games previously scheduled for August 29th against North Shore High School and Shadow Creek High School respectively. This decision was reached after much consideration and consultation with all parties involved.

North Shore is scheduled to face Shadow Creek on August 29th at the Galena Park Stadium.

**Spectator participation guidelines have not been determined and are contingent upon UIL and COVID-19 guidelines.**

An adult assuming responsibility for a minor living separate and apart from a parent, legal guardian, or other person having lawful control under a court order will have to complete an annual Parental Assumption Application.

Applications for the 2020-2021 school year will be available electronically. Due to COVID-19, we are temporarily suspending the notary requirement. An email address is required to complete an online application.

Attach the following documentation to the application:

1.Birth Certificate (required for new Parental Assumption applications)
2.Current Utility Bill (Required)
3.Guardian drivers license or other issued ID
4.Completed Power of Attorney (notarized)
5.Completed Parental Assumption
6.Previous School Records (required for new Parental Assumption applications)

Please click the link to fill out the Parent Assumption Application: https://www.galenaparkisd.com/Page/8309

post_text:
The Residency Affidavit Application is for individuals who cannot produce a property deed/lease or lives with a friend/family member. A new application is required for each school year.
The 2020 - 2021 Residency Affidavit will be available electronically during the designated time frames. Due to COVID-19, we are temporarily suspending the notary requirement.

A completed online application along with all required documents must be attached for approval. A valid email address is required. You will be notified via email if your application is complete and approved.

You must attach the following to the online application:

1.Parent/Guardian Driver's license or other issued ID
2.Homeowner/Landlord/Lessee Driver's license or other issued ID
3. Valid light/gas/water bill or lease in the homeowner/landlord/lessee's name (No disconnect notices)

Click the link to fill out the Residency Affidavit Application: https://www.galenaparkisd.com/Page/8345

post_text:
Nutrition is an important component of learning and keeping our minds strong during the summer months. Galena Park I.S.D. is participating in the Summer Meals Program to provide our students with nutritious meals and snacks when school is not in session.

The Galena Park I.S.D. Student Nutrition Department will be offering summer meals via curbside service; there will be no need to exit your vehicle. All meals are free to anyone 18 or younger. If students are not enrolled in GPISD, the student(s) must be present in the vehicle to receive meals.

Meals will be provided from 10:30 a.m.-12:00 (noon) every Monday, Wednesday and Friday near the bus ramp of each designated campus.

Curbside Pick-Up Locations:
Galena Park Elementary School
Green Valley Elementary School
North Shore Middle School
Sam Houston Elementary School
Dr. Shirley J. Williamson Elementary School
Woodland Acres Elementary School

La nutrición es un componente importante para aprender y mantener nuestras mentes fuertes durante los meses de verano. Galena Park I.S.D. participa en el programa de comidas de verano para proporcionar a nuestros estudiantes comidas y meriendas nutritivas cuando la escuela no está en sesión.

El Departamento de Nutrición del Estudiante de Galena Park I.S.D. ofrecerá comidas de verano a través del servicio en la acera; no habrá necesidad de salir de su vehículo. Todas las comidas son gratuitas para cualquier persona de 18 años o menos.

Las comidas se proporcionarán de 10:30 a.m. a 12:00 p.m. (mediodía) todos los lunes, miércoles y viernes cerca de la rampa de autobús de cada plantel designado.

Lugares de recogida en la acera:

Primaria Woodland Acres
Primaria Sam Houston
Primaria Galena Park
Primaria Green Valley
Primaria Dr. Shirley J. Williamson
Secundaria North Shore

post_text:
GPISD Parents/Guardians,

Galena Park I.S.D. is developing plans for how we will possibly reopen schools for the 2020-2021 school year based on recommendations from state and federal officials, and would like your feedback.

We are committed to providing excellent instruction; therefore, we are planning for three possible scenarios during the 2020-2021 school year:
1. On-campus learning
2. 100% virtual learning
3. Hybrid of on-campus and virtual learning

We will be using the information provided to plan instructional delivery for next year.

Please click on the link below to complete the survey. Please complete one form per student.

Thank you for your support.

prod.galenaparkisd.com/survey

Estimados Padres de familia / Tutores de GPISD:

Galena Park I.S.D. está desarrollando planes sobre cómo posiblemente reabriremos las escuelas para el año escolar 2020-2021 basado en las recomendaciones de las autoridades estatales y federales, y nos gustaría recibir sus comentarios.

Estamos comprometidos en proporcionar una excelente instrucción; por lo tanto, estamos planeando tres posibles escenarios durante el año escolar 2020-2021:

1. Aprendizaje en la escuela
2. Aprendizaje 100% virtual
3. Aprendizaje mixto, en la escuela y virtual

Por favor llene una encuesta por estudiante. Usaremos la información proporcionada para planear la instrucción educativa que se impartirá el próximo año escolar.
Haga clic en el enlace a continuación para completar la encuesta. Por favor llene una encuesta por estudiante.

Gracias por su apoyo.

Let's talk about the 2020 Census!
The census is an enumeration, or an actual count, of the people in the United States to ensure fair representation.

Did you know the Census has only nine questions? The survey takes only 5-10 minutes to complete. It's easy!

You can do your part for the 2020 Census by completing the survey.

post_text:
During National Children's Mental Health Awareness Week, May 4-10, 2020, the Hackett Center for Mental Health and Okay to SayTM are offering 1,000 free at-home screenings of the IndieFlix documentary, "Angst: Raising Awareness Around Anxiety."

This compelling one-hour documentary, which features commentary from tweens, teens, parents and experts - including an interview with world champion swimmer and mental health advocate Michael Phelps – brings new attention to the issue of anxiety and helps viewers identify symptoms and deepen their understanding.

Those who wish to view the film but are not one of the first 1,000 registered will still be able to participate in the May 4-10 screening by registering through the same link and paying a special discounted rate of $4.

The direct link to register for the free in-home viewing is: https://www.showclix.com/event/AngstHouston.

post_text:
We hope you and your family are staying healthy and safe.

If you are experiencing COVID-19 symptoms, there are testing sites in the surrounding areas. Please note, some testing sites are private and costs may vary at each site; there are 3 sites that are entirely free.

-Legacy Northline: 5598 A-1 North Freeway | 832-548-5000 (Sliding scale fee)
-Legacy Santa Clara: East End - 5616 Lawndale | 832-548-5000 (Sliding scale fee)
-Vecinos Clinic at Denver Harbor: 6402 Market St | 713-674-3326 or 713-695-4013 for pediatric care (Cost for mandatory screening varies; test is free)
-Mi Doctor: 5230 Aldine Mail Route; call or text 1-888-776-5252 or call 281-598-3300 (Will bill insurance; $165 without insurance)
-Walgreens (starting tomorrow, Friday, April 17th): 101 W. Southmoore Ave, Pasadena (Free testing)
-Goose Creek ISD Stallworth: 2102 E Archer Rd, Baytown, TX (Free testing)
-Forest Brook Middle School: 7525 Tidwell Rd (Free testing)

“THIS ORGANIZATION AND ITS ACTIVITIES ARE NOT RELATED TO OR SPONSORED BY THE GALENA PARK INDEPENDENT SCHOOL DISTRICT.”

Limited Open Enrollment (LOE) - Allows children who do not live within Galena Park ISD's boundaries to apply for enrollment in Galena Park ISD schools (except closed campuses).

Special Request - A parent of a Galena Park ISD student may submit a Special Request Transfer for their child/children to transfer from a zoned campus to a campus of their choice (except closed campuses). Special request transfers will only be considered during a designated time period for academic, safety and special program reasons.

post_text:
Inscripción Abierta Limitada (LOE, por sus siglas en inglés) - Permite a los niños que no viven dentro de los límites de Galena Park I.S.D. solicitar la inscripción en las escuelas de Galena Park I.S.D. (excepto los planteles que no están aceptando traslados).

Solicitud Especial - Un padre de un estudiante de Galena Park I.S.D. puede pedir una solicitud especial de traslado para que su/s hijo/s se traslade del plantel a donde pertenece/n a un plantel de su elección (excepto los planteles que no están aceptando traslados). Las solicitudes de traslado especial solo se considerarán durante un período de tiempo designado por razones académicas, de seguridad y de programas especiales.

La fecha de distribución final para los paquetes de papel será el MARTES 14 de abril de 2020. Para garantizar que todos los estudiantes tengan los recursos necesarios para el aprendizaje en línea, les brindamos la oportunidad de sacar a préstamo un Chromebook (computadora portátil). La distribución final de Chromebook será el VIERNES 17 de abril de 2020.

Los requisitos para sacar un Chromebook a préstamo incluyen:
1. Debe tener acceso a Internet en el hogar
2. Solo se prestará un dispositivo por domicilio
3. Completar el formulario para sacar a préstamo un Chromebook antes de las 8:00 p.m. el jueves 16 de abril.

Texas, remember the importance of social distancing. If you must go out, avoid public spaces and keep your distance from others (at least 6 feet). If we continue to follow valuable public health guidance, fewer of our friends & family will be affected by COVID-19. #StayHomeTexas

#COVID19 lives on droplets in the lungs of people with the virus, even if they don’t have symptoms. When infected people breathe, the virus enters the air. If you can’t #StayHome, wear a mask/scarf/bandana, stay 6 feet apart, and wash your hands. #DontGoViral

Common symptoms of #COVID19 are fever, dry cough, & shortness of breath. If you have mild symptoms, call your doctor & #StayHome. If you develop serious symptoms, such as trouble breathing, pressure in the chest, or bluish lips or face, call your doctor & seek care immediately.

Los síntomas comunes de #COVID19 son fiebre, tos seca y dificultad para respirar.Si tiene síntomas leves, llame a su médico y quedate en casa.Si desarrolla síntomas graves, como dificultad para respirar o presión en el pecho, busque atención médica de inmediato. #StayHome

Estimados Padres de familia y Tutores de Galena Park I.S.D.:

Para el resto del cierre de escuelas, proporcionaremos una 'Actualización del lunes' para resumir información y mantenerlos actualizados con la información más reciente. Esperamos que se tomen el tiempo de leer detenidamente este boletín.

En la tercera edición de Actualización del lunes encontrará:

1. Mensaje de la Superintendente
2. Cambios a la recogida de comida en la acera
3. Calendario para la recogida de comida de abril
4. Proyecto para estudiantes sobre la Semana de los subdirectores
5. Distribución de paquetes de papel terminará el 14 de abril
6. Blackboard Parentlink: opción para participar / excluirse
7. Apoyo técnico
8. Solicitud de Traslado de Estudiantes - Fechas de Inscripción Abierta
9. Blackboard Parentlink: opción para participar / excluirse
10. Información de consejería
11. Formación del carácter para el mes de abril
12. Manteniéndose conectado con GPISD
13. La palabra del día

Nos gustaría agradecer a todos por su cooperación y paciencia durante este tiempo.

Información importante sobre los paquetes de papel:

La recogida de paquetes de papel se realizará todos los lunes durante el cierre. La recogida de paquetes será entre las 4:00 p.m. y 6:00 p.m. en la Preparatoria Galena Park o en la Preparatoria North Shore Senior.

En las siguientes fotos, encontrará los dos mapas de flujo de tráfico para la Preparatoria Galena Park y la Preparatoria North Shore Senior. Adhiérase a estos mapas cuando recoja los paquetes el lunes.

Si tiene alguna pregunta, envíe un mensaje a la página de Facebook de GPISD o envíe un correo electrónico a communications@galenaparkisd.com.

If you have NOT signed up to receive paper packets and would like to pick up a packet, please click the link below. You will only need to register for the packet once.
www.galenaparkisd.com/form

Paper Packet Pick Up is scheduled for every Monday for the duration of the closure from 4:00 p.m. until 6:00 p.m. at Galena Park High School or North Shore Senior High School.

If you have any questions, please message the GPISD Facebook page or email communications@galenaparkisd.com

NOTE: The link is turned off every Sunday at 11:59 p.m. to allow the curriculum department to prepare for Monday's distribution. The link will be turned back on each Tuesday at noon.

post_text:
Palabra del día: Agallas

Definición:
Pasión y perseverancia hacia metas a muy largo plazo.
Coraje y resolución; fuerza de carácter. (Sustantivo)
"Él demostró las verdaderas agallas de un piloto de la marina".
Sinónimos: coraje, valentía, entereza

Pregunta para reflexionar:
Cuando intentas lograr algo, ¿cómo muestras agallas?

Actividad:
Lee las siguientes afirmaciones, repítelo diariamente:

Tengo grandes expectativas para mí mismo.
Alcanzaré mi potencial.
Soy creativo e imaginativo.
Puedo decirte lo que me apasiona.
Siempre digo gracias cuando la gente me ayuda.
Tengo iniciativa y persigo mis metas.
Tengo un propósito en mi vida.
Tendré una vida exitosa de mi propia elección.

Word of the Day for Thursday, March 19: Confidence

Definition:
Having a strong belief in your own abilities.
The feeling or belief that one can rely on someone or something; firm trust. (Noun)
"We had every confidence in the staff that they would do an excellent job."

Synonyms: trust, belief, faith, credence

Question for Reflection:
When do you feel most confident?

Activity:
Make a list of things you are good at. Spend time doing them. Trying hard is easier when you feel confident!

#WordOfTheDay #GalenaParkISDExcellence

Palabra del día: Confianza

Definición:
Tener absoluta confianza en tus propias habilidades.
La sensación o la creencia de que uno puede confiar en alguien o algo; confianza plena. (Sustantivo)
"Teníamos toda la confianza en el personal de que harían un excelente trabajo".
Sinónimos: creencia, convicción, fe, credibilidad

Pregunta para reflexionar:
¿Cuándo te sientes más seguro?

Actividad:
Haz una lista de las cosas en las que eres bueno. Pasa tiempo haciéndolas. ¡Esforzarse es más fácil cuando te sientes seguro!

Definition:
A hope or ambition of achieving something.
The object of one's hope or ambition; a goal. (Noun)
“Her aspiration is to be an engineer and work with the space program.

”Synonyms: desire, hope, longing, yearning, hankering, urge, wish, aim, ambition, expectation, inclination, objective, goal, target, dream

Question for Reflection:
How are you preparing today to make sure you reach your goals?

Activity:
Write about a dream you have of achieving something great in the future.

#WordOfTheDay #GalenaParkISDExcellence

A hope or ambition of achieving something.
The object of one's hope or ambition; a goal. (Noun)
“Her aspiration is to be an engineer and work with the space program.

”Synonyms: desire, hope, longing, yearning, hankering, urge, wish, aim, ambition, expectation, inclination, objective, goal, target, dream

Question for Reflection:
How are you preparing today to make sure you reach your goals?

Activity:
Write about a dream you have of achieving something great in the future.

#WordOfTheDay #GalenaParkISDExcellence

Palabra del día: Resistencia

Definición:
La capacidad de recuperarse rápidamente de las dificultades, dureza.
La capacidad de una sustancia u objeto para recuperar su forma; elasticidad.
Soler a recuperarse fácilmente de la desgracia o el cambio. (Sustantivo)
"El nylon es excelente en capacidad de desgaste y resistencia".
Sinónimos: durabilidad, flexibilidad, maleabilidad, plasticidad

Word of the Day for Tuesday, March 17: Resilience

Definition:
The capacity to recover quickly from difficulties, toughness.
The ability of a substance or object to spring back into shape; elasticity.
Tending to recover easily from misfortune or change. (Noun)
"Nylon is excellent in wearability and resilience."

Synonyms: durability, flexibility, pliability, plasticity

Question for Reflection:
Do you know of someone who doesn’t give up?

Activity:
Write about a time when you didn’t give up.

#WordOfTheDay #GalenaParkISDExcellence

Cobb’s Math & Science Club Students competed at Pearland Junior High West School’s TMSCA State Qualifier Competition on Saturday against schools from The Village School, Fort Settlement, First Colony, River Oaks Baptist School, Quail Valley Middle, The Mandarin Immersion Magnet School, Sartartia Middle, Pearland West, private and home-schooled students.

In Number Sense, Jase Tapiz received the 7th place ribbon.

In Calculator, Jase Tapiz received the 2nd place trophy, Maria Gomez received a 10th place ribbon and qualified for state competition, Abigail Ortiz received an 8th place ribbon. These students all scored over the 160 state qualifying score.

In General Math, Jase Tapiz scored a 144 which qualified him for state and an 82 in science which allows him to compete in all (4) categories in San Antonio.

Way to go, Cobb Cougars! YOU MADE US PROUD!!! Next, students will be competing at Beaumont Odom for Regional.

#GalenaParkISDExcellence

Cobb Sixth Grade Campus held their Campus Science Fair yesterday!
The students presented their Scientific Investigatory Projects and were critiqued by several judges pertaining to their topics.

The students competed in five categories—Biology, Consumer Science, Chemistry, Physics and Behavioral Science.

text: GPISD se enorgullece en anunciar la implementación en todo el distrito de pre-kínder de día completo en el otoño de 2020. Los estudiantes de pre-kínder se benefician de mayores niveles de preparación escolar, con mayores habilidades cognitivas y de alfabetización, así como del desarrollo socioemocional. Si desea obtener más información sobre este maravilloso programa, consulte el folleto adjunto.

We would like to thank all the families who came out to the 2nd Annual GPISD Bilingual/ESL Family Engagement Day on Saturday.
Students and their families heard from our guest speaker, Dr. Jose Luis Zelaya, who shared his amazing journey of perseverance to accomplish the highest level in education, a doctoral degree from Texas A&M.
We also had an outstanding panel of recent GPISD graduates who shared their own experiences and provided words of wisdom for students. Parents attended sessions to help them understand student assessments, high school credits, graduation requirements and college opportunities.
#GalenaParkISDExcellence

The students at Galena Park Elementary are sipping on some Starbooks to help with their reading challenge!
The students are rotating to each table with different genres and sip on a book. Once they find a book to read, the students use the seesaw app to write the title and take a picture of the book. When they come back to the library and need help looking for a specific genre they can log in to the app to see the ones they liked.
Great job Ms. Resendez and Ms. Gudiel on motivating the students at GPE. What an awesome idea!

On Saturday, the Cobb 6th Grade Campus Math & Science Club competed at Doerre Intermediate School.

In number sense Cobb’s rankings were: Jase Tapiz received a 4th place trophy and scored a state-qualifying score

In calculator: Jase Tapiz received the 2nd place trophy and Abigail Ortiz tied with two other students for 9th place

In general math: Jase Tapiz received the 8th place medal with a state-qualifying score

In science: Alejandro Martinez received the 10th place medal.

Other students competing were Evelyn Arredondo, Dember Cosme, Itzel Cruz, Katherine Elizondo, Maria Gomez, Jose Grimaldo, Jose Jimenez, Alexis Lewis, Abigail Ortiz, Sean Rojas, Nery Serrano, Andrew Thomas, and Aryana Wehmeyer.

Congratulations to all of the students and thanks to the Tapiz family for bringing snacks and drinks for all of the students.
#GalenaParkISDExcellence

post_text:
Yesterday, Purple Sage Elementary 5th grade Bulldogs had an exciting day attending their first day of STARBASE at Ellington Field.
STARBASE is a Department of Defense Youth Program that focuses on STEM education. Students learned how to find coordinates on GPS devices while geocaching for hidden items and how to interpret earth's elements on the Periodic Table. They also built molecular models and explored how energy can be transferred from one form to another. It was a GREAT day to be a PSE Bulldog! #GalenaParkISDExcellence #STARBASE #ElemSTEM #PSEStrong

Last week, North Shore 10th Grade Center celebrated Kindness Week. NS10 students were celebrated for being kind and encouraged to thank others who have shown them kindness this school year.

The campus also showed kindness to their community by hosting a food drive for North Channel Assistance Ministries. Sophomore students brought non-perishable food items to their 2nd-period class, the students brought in over 649 items! Mr. Gordon and Mrs. Guillory's classes were treated to a pizza party for having the most donation. Thanks to North Channel Assistance Ministries for providing the pizza!

A big thank you to Ms. Wagner and the counseling team for making Kindness Week a success! Way to Go, Mustangs!
#GalenaParkISDExcellence #Made4Greatness #NSSophomoreYear

post_text:
Last Saturday, Cobb 6th Grade Campus took 60 Demoiselle Diamonds and Distinguished Debonairs to visit Texas Southern University for Tiger Paw Day!
The purpose of this field trip was to give students an opportunity to start thinking about college and possible career choices. The students learned about the campus' history as well as the various degrees the university offers. They actively participated in trivia games about the university and even won awesome prizes.
After the presentations, the students went on a guided tour of the campus, they were escorted by current students attending TSU. Each student was given a free ticket to the TSU football game at the BBVA Compass Stadium where students even got to take a few pictures with the TSU mascots, Rex, Tex, and Lex.
#GalenaParkISDExcellence #CollegeReadiness

Galena Park ISD added 47 new photos.
November 11, 2019 at 9:17 AM ·

It was the final day of National Children’s Book Week and National STEM/STEAM Day. The students have been working with the book, "I Got A Chicken for My Birthday", which is about a girl who asks her Abuela for tickets to an amusement park but gets a chicken instead. In a funny turn of events, the chicken ends up building an amusement park for the girl.
After the story, the students were given two sizes of cups, craft sticks, pipe cleaners, and clothespins to construct their own roller coaster.

There will be more roller coaster coming, so be on the lookout!
#GalenaParkISDExcellence

post_text:
On Wednesday, October 30th, 74 students from Galena Park High School and North Shore Senior High visited the campuses of the University of Houston – Downtown and Texas Southern University. The students were escorted by the Academic Advisors, Mrs. Couch and Mrs.Hardin, along with their counselors: Mrs. Galloway and Mrs. Ojeda. The students eagerly listened to admissions presentations and took campus tours. The purpose of the field experience was to encourage students to apply to four-year universities and to see their potential for higher education. This field experience provided students the opportunity to expand upon their education by exploring options for career advancement. The University of Houston - Downtown showcased for the students the theatrical department and opportunities available in the future for those careers. Texas Southern University exposed the students to the School of Law and the Pharmacy departments that are well known internationally for student success.
#GalenaParkISDExcellence #CollegeReadiness

On Friday, November 1st, the Cobb Sixth Grade Campus Demoiselle Diamonds and Distinguished Debonair organizations had their induction ceremony. The Diamonds welcomed 64 young ladies and the Debonairs welcomed 20 young boys all ready to serve. Special thank you to the Sponsors Mr. Segeada, Mr. Drysdale, Ms. Aguirre, Mrs. Meeks, Ms. Priestley, Mrs. Tibbs, Mrs. Woods as well as parents and family members that were in attendance. Thank you to Ms. Alondria Brooks for making the mini mums and boutonnieres for the ceremony. Thank you to Mr. Hurtado for coming and speaking to the inductees.
Cobb is ready to get the year started with the newly inducted members.
#GalenaParkISDExcellence

Ladies, remember to always shine bright like a diamond and boys remember being a gentleman never gets old.
